@startuml AD_D07_Emergency_Patient_Search

title AD_D07 — Search Patient by ID or Name (Emergency Access)

|Doctor|
|System|

|Doctor|

note
  Prerequisites:
  - Doctor is authenticated
  - Target patient is registered in system
  - Patient is NOT on doctor's assigned list
end note

start

:Type patient name or Patient ID\ninto global search bar;

|System|

:Search all registered patient records\n(not restricted to assigned list);

if (Patient found?) then (no)
  :Display "No matching patient\nrecord found";\nSuggest verifying ID with Administrator;
  |Doctor|
  stop
else (yes)
  :Return results list:\n- Patient name\n- Patient ID\n- Date of birth (partially masked)\n- Assigned doctor name;
endif

|Doctor|

:Select target patient from results;

|System|

:Intercept navigation;\nDisplay mandatory "Emergency Access" modal:\n"You are about to access a patient\nnot assigned to you.\nThis access will be logged and the\nassigned doctor will be notified.\nPlease state your clinical reason.";

|Doctor|

if (Enter clinical reason\nand confirm?) then (no — cancelled)
  |System|
  :Block access;\nLog attempt as "Declined by User";
  stop
else (yes)
endif

if (Reason ≥ 10 characters?) then (no)
  |System|
  :Reject submission;\nHighlight minimum character requirement;
  |Doctor|
  :Enter longer reason;
  |System|
else (yes)
endif

:Grant read-only access\nto patient full record\nfor current session only;
:Create immutable audit log entry:\n- Requesting doctor ID\n- Patient ID\n- Timestamp\n- Stated reason;
:Send automated notification\nto patient's assigned doctor;

|Doctor|

:View patient record\n(read-only);

stop

@enduml
